Package edu.kit.unwwi.checkpoints.qmp.commands

Klasse ELFDump

java.lang.Object
edu.kit.unwwi.checkpoints.qmp.commands.ELFDump
Alle implementierten Schnittstellen:
Command, EventHandler
public class ELFDump extends Object implements EventHandler, Command
This class dumps the current memory data from a QEMU-instance to disk in ELF format.

  • Konstruktordetails

    • ELFDump

      public ELFDump(@NotNull @NotNull QMPInterface instance)
      Creates a new ELFDump object which can be executed later. Needs the QMPInterface because this is an asynchronous request, which means the object needs to receive information from the Interface at some point.
      Parameter:
      instance - The QMPinterface to receive the event from.

  • Methodendetails

      temp - The Path to use for temporary files.

    • eventName

      @NotNull public @NotNull String eventName()
      Beschreibung aus Schnittstelle kopiert: EventHandler
      This method returns the type of Event QEMU reports in its message. QMPInterface only calls the handleEvent method for EventHandlers where the reported name from QEMU and the return of this method match.
      Angegeben von:
      eventName in Schnittstelle EventHandler
